{"title_page": "Cathy Bakewell, Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox office holder\n\n|honorific_prefix =  [[The Right Honourable]]\n|name = The Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville\n|image = Official portrait of Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville crop 2.jpg\n|caption =  \n| honorific_suffix = [[MBE]]\n|office = [[Members of the House of Lords|Member of the House of Lords]]<br>[[Lord Temporal]]\n|term_start = 15 October 2013<br>[[Life Peerage]]\n|term_end = \n|office1           = Leader of [[Somerset County Council]]\n|term_start1       = 2001\n|term_end1         = 2007\n|predecessor1      = \n|successor1        = \n|office2      = [[Somerset County Council]]lor<br>for Coker Ward\n|term_start2  =  6 May 1993\n|term_end2    =  2 May 2013\n|predecessor2 = \n|successor2   =  \n|office3      = [[South Somerset District Council]]lor<br>for Coker Ward\n|term_start3  =  4 June 2009\n|term_end3    =  2 May 2019\n|predecessor3 = \n|successor3   =  \n|birth_name       =  Catherine Mary Green<ref name=\"GlasConvent\">{{cite web|title=Messages and Memories|url=http://www.stlouisconvent.co.uk/messages.html|website=Remembering St. Louis, Glastonbury Convent|accessdate=24 August 2016|date=31 October 2014}}</ref>\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1949|3|7|df=yes}}\n|birth_place      = [[Bristol]], England\n|occupation = Politician\n|party = [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]\n}}\n\n'''Catherine Mary Bakewell, Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville''', {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|MBE}} (born 7 March 1949<ref>{{cite web|title=Councillor Catherine Mary Bakewell|url=https://www.duedil.com/director/905497842/catherine-mary-bakewell|publisher=duedil.com|accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref>), known as '''Cathy Bakewell''', is a British politician who is a [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] member of the [[House of Lords]] and formerly an elected District Councillor for the Coker ward of [[South Somerset]].\n\n==Early life and career==\nBakewell was born Catherine Mary Green in [[Bristol]] in 1949.<ref name=\"LibDemSite\">{{cite web|title=Cathy Bakewell|url=http://www.libdems.org.uk/cathy_bakewell|website=Liberal Democrats|accessdate=24 August 2016|date=2014-01-22}}</ref> Bakewell joined the Liberal Party in 1974. She became the [[Yeovil]] Constituency Secretary and then went on to become to be an assistant to Yeovil [[Member of parliament]] [[Paddy Ashdown]]. Bakewell worked with Ashdown for twenty years eventually running the Leader's Office after the [[1997 United Kingdom general election|1997 elections]].<ref name=\"Ashdown2010\">{{cite book|last1=Ashdown|first1=Paddy|title=A Fortunate Life: The Autobiography of Paddy Ashdown|date=2010|publisher=Aurum Press|isbn=978-1845136475|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=_DrLAgAAQBAJ&lpg=PT225&dq=%22paddy%20ashdown%22%20%22cathy%20bakewell%22&pg=PT225#v=onepage&q=%20%22cathy%20bakewell%22&f=false}}</ref>\n\nBakewell was first elected to [[Somerset County Council]] in 1993, serving as Leader from 2001 to 2007, standing down in 2013.<ref name=\"LibDemAug2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.libdemvoice.org/so-who-are-these-new-liberal-democrat-peers-then-35584.html|title=So, who are these new Liberal Democrat peers, then?|date=1 August 2013|website=Liberal Democrat Voice|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"SSDCAug2013\">{{cite web|title=South Somerset District Council Councillor Cathy Bakewell to become Baroness |url=http://www.southsomerset.gov.uk/latest-news/august-2013/south-somerset-district-council-councillor-cathy-bakewell-to-become-baroness/ |website=South Somerset District Council |accessdate=24 August 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214123037/http://www.southsomerset.gov.uk/latest-news/august-2013/south-somerset-district-council-councillor-cathy-bakewell-to-become-baroness/ |archivedate=14 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=\"westerngaz\">{{cite web|url=http://www.westerngazette.co.uk/Coker-councillor-Cathy-Bakewell-thrilled-named/story-19605479-detail/story.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20131214113040/http://www.westerngazette.co.uk/Coker-councillor-Cathy-Bakewell-thrilled-named/story-19605479-detail/story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=14 December 2013|title=Coker councillor Cathy Bakewell \"thrilled\" to be named as Baroness|date=2 August 2013|publisher=Western Gazette|accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref> Bakewell was a member of the 2007 Councillors Commission which investigated the incentives and barriers to serving on Local Authorities.<ref name=\"LGIU2007\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lgiu.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Councillors-Commission-Begins-Work-04-2007.pdf|title=Councillors Commission begins work (LGiU)|date=10 April 2007|website=Local Government Information Unit|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nBakewell has served as a Liberal Democrat District Councillor for the Coker [[Wards and electoral divisions of the United Kingdom|electoral ward]] in [[South Somerset]] since 2009.<ref name=\"SSDC\">{{cite web|url=http://modgov.southsomerset.gov.uk/mgUserInfo.aspx?UID=39|title=Councillor details - Councillor Cathy Bakewell|website=South Somerset District Council|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ThisIsNov2013\" />\n\nOn 9 September 2013, Bakewell was created a [[life peer]] as '''Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville''', of [[Hardington Mandeville]] in the [[County of Somerset]],<ref>{{London Gazette\n| issue = 60624\n| date = 11 September 2013\n|page=17949\n}}</ref> taking her title for the local village of [[Hardington Mandeville]] where she lives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.southsomerset.gov.uk/councillors-and-democracy/councillors/find-your-local-councillor/cllr-cathy-bakewell|title=Cllr Cathy Bakewell|publisher=South Somerset Council|accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref> She made her maiden speech in the [[House of Lords]] that November during a debate on housing, the speech addressed affordable housing and the impact of the [[under-occupancy penalty|under-occupancy charge]].<ref name=\"ThisIsNov2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisthewestcountry.co.uk/news/10779940.Baroness_Bakewell_makes_maiden_speech_in_Lords/|title=Baroness Bakewell makes maiden speech in Lords|date=1 November 2013|website=thisisthewestcountry.co.uk|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref> She served as a director for the [[Local Government Leadership|Leadership Centre for Local Government]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.localleadership.gov.uk/about/whoweare|title=Who we are|publisher=Leadership Centre|accessdate=14 December 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20140320231742/http://www.localleadership.gov.uk/about/whoweare|archive-date=20 March 2014|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Current Liberal Democrat Peers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville, Cathy Bakewell, Baroness}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Female life peers]]\n[[Category:Liberal Democrats (UK) life peers]]\n[[Category:Members of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Bristol]]\n[[Category:Councillors in Somerset]]\n[[Category:Liberal Democrats (UK) councillors]]\n[[Category:Leaders of local authorities of England]]\n\n{{Life-peer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox office holder\n\n|honorific_prefix =  [[The Right Honourable]]\n|name = The Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville\n|image = Official portrait of Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville crop 2.jpg\n|caption =  \n| honorific_suffix = [[MBE]]\n|office = [[Members of the House of Lords|Member of the House of Lords]]<br>[[Lord Temporal]]\n|term_start = 15 October 2013<br>[[Life Peerage]]\n|term_end = \n|office1           = Leader of [[Somerset County Council]]\n|term_start1       = 2001\n|term_end1         = 2007\n|predecessor1      = \n|successor1        = \n|office2      = [[Somerset County Council]]lor<br>for Coker Ward\n|term_start2  =  6 May 1993\n|term_end2    =  2 May 2013\n|predecessor2 = \n|successor2   =  \n|office3      = [[South Somerset District Council]]lor<br>for Coker Ward\n|term_start3  =  4 June 2009\n|term_end3    =  2 May 2019\n|predecessor3 = \n|successor3   =  \n|birth_name       =  Catherine Mary Green<ref name=\"GlasConvent\">{{cite web|title=Messages and Memories|url=http://www.stlouisconvent.co.uk/messages.html|website=Remembering St. Louis, Glastonbury Convent|accessdate=24 August 2016|date=31 October 2014}}</ref>\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1949|3|7|df=yes}}\n|birth_place      = [[Bristol]], England\n|occupation = Politician\n|party = [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]\n}}\n\n'''Catherine Mary Bakewell, Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville''', {{post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|MBE}} (born 7 March 1949<ref>{{cite web|title=Councillor Catherine Mary Bakewell|url=https://www.duedil.com/director/905497842/catherine-mary-bakewell|publisher=duedil.com|accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref>), known as '''Cathy Bakewell''', is a British politician who is a [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrat]] member of the [[House of Lords]] and formerly an elected District Councillor for the Coker ward of [[South Somerset]].\n\n==Early life and career==\nBakewell was born Catherine Mary Green in [[Bristol]] in 1949.<ref name=\"LibDemSite\">{{cite web|title=Cathy Bakewell|url=http://www.libdems.org.uk/cathy_bakewell|website=Liberal Democrats|accessdate=24 August 2016|date=2014-01-22}}</ref> Bakewell joined the Liberal Party in 1974. She became the [[Yeovil]] Constituency Secretary and then went on to become to be an assistant to Yeovil [[Member of parliament]] [[Paddy Ashdown]]. Bakewell worked with Ashdown for twenty years eventually running the Leader's Office after the [[1997 United Kingdom general election|1997 elections]].<ref name=\"Ashdown2010\">{{cite book|last1=Ashdown|first1=Paddy|title=A Fortunate Life: The Autobiography of Paddy Ashdown|date=2010|publisher=Aurum Press|isbn=978-1845136475|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=_DrLAgAAQBAJ&lpg=PT225&dq=%22paddy%20ashdown%22%20%22cathy%20bakewell%22&pg=PT225#v=onepage&q=%20%22cathy%20bakewell%22&f=false}}</ref>\n\nBakewell was first elected to [[Somerset County Council]] in 1993, serving as Leader from 2001 to 2007, standing down in 2013.<ref name=\"LibDemAug2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.libdemvoice.org/so-who-are-these-new-liberal-democrat-peers-then-35584.html|title=So, who are these new Liberal Democrat peers, then?|date=1 August 2013|website=Liberal Democrat Voice|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"SSDCAug2013\">{{cite web|title=South Somerset District Council Councillor Cathy Bakewell to become Baroness |url=http://www.southsomerset.gov.uk/latest-news/august-2013/south-somerset-district-council-councillor-cathy-bakewell-to-become-baroness/ |website=South Somerset District Council |accessdate=24 August 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214123037/http://www.southsomerset.gov.uk/latest-news/august-2013/south-somerset-district-council-councillor-cathy-bakewell-to-become-baroness/ |archivedate=14 December 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=\"westerngaz\">{{cite web|url=http://www.westerngazette.co.uk/Coker-councillor-Cathy-Bakewell-thrilled-named/story-19605479-detail/story.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20131214113040/http://www.westerngazette.co.uk/Coker-councillor-Cathy-Bakewell-thrilled-named/story-19605479-detail/story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=14 December 2013|title=Coker councillor Cathy Bakewell \"thrilled\" to be named as Baroness|date=2 August 2013|publisher=Western Gazette|accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref> Bakewell was a member of the 2007 Councillors Commission which investigated the incentives and barriers to serving on Local Authorities.<ref name=\"LGIU2007\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lgiu.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Councillors-Commission-Begins-Work-04-2007.pdf|title=Councillors Commission begins work (LGiU)|date=10 April 2007|website=Local Government Information Unit|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>\n\nBakewell has served as a Liberal Democrat District Councillor for the Coker [[Wards and electoral divisions of the United Kingdom|electoral ward]] in [[South Somerset]] since 2009.<ref name=\"SSDC\">{{cite web|url=http://modgov.southsomerset.gov.uk/mgUserInfo.aspx?UID=39|title=Councillor details - Councillor Cathy Bakewell|website=South Somerset District Council|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"ThisIsNov2013\" />\n\nOn 9 September 2013, Bakewell was created a [[life peer]] as '''Baroness Bakewell of Hardington Mandeville''', of [[Hardington Mandeville]] in the [[County of Somerset]],<ref>{{London Gazette\n| issue = 60624\n| date = 11 September 2013\n|page=17949\n}}</ref> taking her title for the local village of [[Hardington Mandeville]] where she lives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.southsomerset.gov.uk/councillors-and-democracy/councillors/find-your-local-councillor/cllr-cathy-bakewell|title=Cllr Cathy Bakewell|publisher=South Somerset Council|accessdate=14 December 2013}}</ref> She made her maiden speech in the [[House of Lords]] that November during a debate on housing, the speech addressed affordable housing and the impact of the [[under-occupancy penalty|under-occupancy charge]].<ref name=\"ThisIsNov2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisthewestcountry.co.uk/news/10779940.Baroness_Bakewell_makes_maiden_speech_in_Lords/|title=Baroness Bakewell makes maiden speech in Lords|date=1 November 2013|website=thisisthewestcountry.co.uk|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref> She served as a director for the [[Local Government Leadership|Leadership Centre for Local Government]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.localleadership.gov.uk/about/whoweare|title=Who we are|publisher=Leadership Centr