mSeason\n| mode = football\n| year = 1883\n| team = Harvard Crimson\n| image = \n| image_size =  \n| conference = Independent\n| division = \n| short_conf =  \n| record = 8\u20132\n| conf_record = \n| head_coach = No coach\n| hc_year = \n| off_scheme = \n| def_scheme = \n| stadium=\n| champion =  \n}}\n{{1883 college football records}}\nThe '''1883 Harvard Crimson football team''' represented [[Harvard University]] in the [[1883 college football season]]. The team compiled an 8\u20132 record, losing its rivalry games against both [[1883 Princeton Tigers football team|Princeton]] and [[1883 Yale Bulldogs football team|Yale]]. Randolph M. Appleton was the team captain.<ref name=SR>{{cite web|title=1883 Harvard Crimson Schedule and Results|publisher=Sports Reference LLC|work=SR/College Football|accessdate=February 27, 2017|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/harvard/1883-schedule.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gocrimson.com/sports/fball/history/Media_Center_Football_Yearly_Results |title=Harvard Football Yearly Records|work=GoCrimson.com |publisher=Harvard University |accessdate=August 13, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n\n{{CFB schedule\n|attend=yes\n|source=yes\n\n|October 6| |{{cfb link|year=1883|team=Wesleyan Methodists|title=Wesleyan}}|Jarvis Field|[[Cambridge, Massachusetts|Cambridge]], Massachusetts|W 23\u20131| |<ref>{{cite news|title=Foot-Ball at Cambridge: Harvard Defeats Wesleyan in the First Game of the Season|newspaper=The New York Times|date=October 7, 1883|page=2|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/16389513/football_at_cambridge_harvard_defeats/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|October 13| |[[1883 Penn Quakers football team|Penn]] ([[Harvard\u2013Penn football rivalry|rivalry]])|Jarvis Field,|Cambridge, Massachusetts|W 4\u20130| |<ref>{{cite news|title=Foot-Ball at Cambridge: The Match Between Harvard and the University of Pennsylvania|newspaper=The New York Times|date=October 14, 1883|page=9|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/1